reviewText:
From a walk in Griffith Park to yoga to African Dance for expectant mothers, this has something for everyone.

Personally, I love this episode, but I may be a little biased, as "Baby Werkman" is my son.  He's 10 years old now, doing well in school, and if he can't be a NY Yankee, he wants to be an inventor... just in case you were interested.  Hey, this is better than a blog!
